      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;use-github-pull-requests&#34;&gt;Use GitHub Pull Requests&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Keep pull requests small and focused.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Summarize the change and the rationale.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Request reviews from relevant collaborators.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Merge after checks pass and feedback is addressed.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Issues and Pull Requests</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/software/domains/github/texts/issues-and-pull-requests/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/software/domains/github/texts/issues-and-pull-requests/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Issues capture tasks and discussions. Pull requests bundle changes for review&#xA;before merging.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Clear issue descriptions and small pull requests improve review quality.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>What is GitHub?</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/software/domains/github/texts/what-is-github/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/domains/computing/domains/software/domains/github/texts/what-is-github/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;GitHub is a hosted platform for git repositories with collaboration features&#xA;such as issues, pull requests, and code review.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
